			h1.casestudy__head Public Interest Registry .ngo Domain Guide
			.casestudy__body
				p PIR works behind-the-scenes administering the top-level domains .org, .ngo and .ong. While .org domains have open registration, .ngo and .ong domains are reserved for registered nonprofits and international NGOs. PIR approached me to design a short guide to their .ngo and .ong domains, from the registration process to the benefits of acquiring one. Parts of this guide were translated to French, German and Portuguese. 
			blockquote.casestudy__quote &ldquo;Maria delivers high quality design work in a timely manner. I have had the pleasure of working with Maria for the past 4 years, and she's continued to help PIR raise its own standards.&rdquo;
			cite.casestudy__citation Megan Soffer, Marketing and Social Media Manager
		.casestudy__image
			img(src="/img/pir-domain-guide-2.jpg")
